cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper deals with adversarial examples in Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and proposes a mechanism based on foveations to alleviate them. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the hypothesis that CNNs act locally linearly to changes in image regions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the robustness of CNNs to transformations, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy issues related to adversarial examples, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
